# Architecture Decision Record: {{projectName}}

> Status: generated by `@nakedev/go-scaffold`
> Scope: initial scaffold

## 1. Topology

**Decision:** Single Go binary (`cmd/api`), REST over Gin.
**Rationale:** One process serves all domains; a second entry point
(`cmd/worker`, `cmd/migrate`) gets its own `main.go` only once there's a real
second process ‚Äî `main.go` has no importers, so adding one later touches no
other file.

## 2. Package Layout

```text
cmd/
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ api/main.go             # config, slog, graceful shutdown, wires domains
internal/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ platform/                # talks to real external systems (DB, later: cache, queue, mail, ...)
‚îÇ   ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ database/
‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ shared/                  # pure logic/framework glue, no I/O
‚îÇ   ‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ config/  apperror/  dberr/  httpx/  middleware/  pagination/
‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ app/                     # domain packages (one per feature)
    ‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ <domain>/
```

**Decision:** `platform/` vs `shared/` is split by whether the code talks to
a real external system.
**Rationale:** Code that does I/O against Postgres/cache/queue/SMTP/S3 ‚Üí
`platform/`. Pure logic or HTTP-framework glue with no I/O ‚Üí `shared/`. Never
add a `shared/utils` or similarly generic package ‚Äî name it after what it
actually does.

## 3. API Style

**Decision:** REST over Gin, one handler package per domain, routes grouped
under {{#if versioning}}`/v1`, `/v2`, etc. ‚Äî one group per version folder in use{{else}}`/v1`{{/if}}.
**Rationale:** `handler ‚Üí service ‚Üí repository`, one direction, all three
layers in the same package ‚Äî no cross-domain imports.

## 4. Response and Error Model

**Decision:** Central `apperror.AppError` (HTTP status + machine-readable
`code` + message), rendered once by `middleware.Error()`.
**Rationale:** Handlers only ever do `c.Error(err); return` ‚Äî no `c.JSON` per
call site, no error-shape drift between domains.

- Domain-specific errors live in each package's `errors.go` (e.g.
  `USER_NOT_FOUND`, not a bare `NOT_FOUND`)
- DB errors are classified once in `shared/dberr` (`IsDuplicate`,
  `IsForeignKey`) and mapped to the right HTTP status per domain

## 5. Module Versioning

{{#if versioning}}
**Decision:** Folder-based domain versioning is enabled ‚Äî routes are real
per-version, not just folder layout.
**Rationale:** `internal/app/v1/<domain>`, `v2/<domain>`, etc., each gets its
own `r.Group("/v1")` / `r.Group("/v2")` and a version-qualified import alias
(`<domain>v1`, `<domain>v2`) in `cmd/api/main.go`. That means **the same
domain name can live in more than one version at once** ‚Äî
`v1/orders` and `v2/orders` coexisting with different behavior is the actual
point of versioning, not a naming collision. `go-scaffold generate module
<name> --module-version v2` targets a specific folder; omit the flag and the
CLI asks which version (or lets you create a new one) once more than one
exists. A migration is shared between versions of the same domain (same
table, different API shape) until no version references it anymore.
{{else}}
**Decision:** No folder-based versioning ‚Äî domains live directly under
`internal/app/<domain>`, routes under `/v1`.
**Rationale:** Simplest layout until an actual breaking API version is
needed. This is a `create`-time choice ‚Äî toggling `versioning` in
`go-scaffold.config.json` by hand doesn't move existing domains into a
version folder, it just makes the *next* `generate module` create one while
old domains stay put. Re-scaffold (or move domains by hand) instead of
flipping the flag on an existing project.
{{/if}}

## 6. Pagination

**Decision:** Shared `limit`/`offset` parsing and response envelope
(`shared/pagination`), used by every list endpoint.
**Rationale:** One implementation, one response shape (`{data, limit,
offset}`) ‚Äî no per-domain reinvention.

## 7. Persistence

**Decision:** PostgreSQL + GORM, schema managed by
[golang-migrate](https://github.com/golang-migrate/migrate).
**Rationale:** `AUTO_MIGRATE=true` runs GORM's AutoMigrate in dev for speed;
prod runs `migrate up` as a separate, versioned, rollback-capable step ‚Äî
AutoMigrate is add-only and locks tables once there's real data.

{{#if docker}}- `docker-compose.yml` provides the local Postgres instance
{{/if}}
## 8. IDs

**Decision:** UUID v7 for every entity, generated app-side
(`shared/id.New()`), not by a DB default.
**Rationale:** Time-ordered IDs sort by creation time, reducing B-tree page
splits versus random v4 under heavy writes ‚Äî and the app has the ID before
insert, so it doesn't need `gen_random_uuid()`.

{{#if openapiDocs}}
## 9. API Documentation

**Decision:** Hand-written OpenAPI spec (`docs/openapi.yaml`), split by
domain module, served as a static file at `/openapi.yaml`.
**Rationale:** Cheap while the endpoint count is low; switch to
comment-generated (swaggo) if hand-updates start drifting.
{{/if}}

